courses.learning_outcomes:
1. To apply fundamental knowledge in quantum physics, statistical physics, and solid state physics to understand the technologically important semiconducting materials;
2. To develop a comprehensive understanding of the physics of semiconductors and a physical sense on why semiconductors are useful;
3. To apply physical principles to understand the physics behind typical semiconductor devices;
4. To apply physical principles to understand the physics behind low dimensional semiconductor heterostructures and their applications.

